        <div id="collapseSexual" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingSexual" data-parent="#laws-section">
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>Sexual abuse laws safeguard against sexual assault, harassment, and exploitation. Key legal provisions include:</p>
                <ol style="font-size: 20px;">
                    <li><h4>Indian Penal Code (IPC), 1860</h4></li>
                         <ul>
                            <li><b>Section 354: </b>Outlaws assault or criminal force used to outrage a woman’s modesty.</li>
                            <li><b>Section 354A: </b>Defines and punishes sexual harassment, including unwelcome physical contact, advances, and sexually colored remarks.</li>
                            <li><b>Section 354B: </b>Punishes assault or use of criminal force to disrobe a woman.</li>
                            <li><b>Section 375: </b> Defines rape and its various forms, including sexual intercourse without consent.</li>
                            <li><b>Section 376: </b>Provides punishment for rape, with stringent penalties including life imprisonment.</li>
                            <li><b>Section 376C: </b> Addresses sexual abuse by people in authority (e.g., public servants, managers).</li>
                            <li><b>Section 376D: </b>Punishes gang rape, with more severe penalties.</li>
                            <li><b>Section 509: </b>Punishes acts intended to insult the modesty of a woman, including verbal or physical harassment of a sexual nature.</li>


                        </ul>
                        <br>
                    <li><h4>The Protection of Children from Sexual Offences(POCSO) Act, 2012</h4></li>
                    <p>
                        Protects minors from sexual abuse, including sexual assault, harassment, and pornography, with specific provisions for aggravated cases.
                    </p>
                    <li><h4>Criminal Law (Amendment) Act, 2013 (Nirbhaya Act)</h4></li>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Strengthened the laws for sexual violence, making punishment for rape, gang rape, and other forms of sexual assault more stringent.</li>
                            <li>Introduced Section 354C (voyeurism) and Section 354D (stalking), which cover forms of sexual abuse related to observation and following with sexual intent.</li>


                        </ul>
                        <br>
                    <li><h4>The Sexual Harassment of Women at Workplace (Prevention, Prohibition, and Redressal) Act, 2013</h4></li>
                    <p>Specifically addresses sexual harassment at the workplace, offering protection and remedies for women facing abuse in professional settings.</p>
                    <li><h4>The Immoral Traffic (Prevention) Act, 1956</h4></li>
                       <ul>
                           <li>Deals with sexual abuse in the context of trafficking, particularly addressing exploitation and abuse related to forced prostitution.</li>
                           <li>These laws cover various forms of sexual abuse, providing women with legal recourse for protection and justice.</li>
                       </ul>
                </ol>
