    <div id="collapseCyber" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingCyber" data-parent="#laws-section">
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>Cyber abuse laws protect individuals from online harassment, stalking, and exploitation. Key legal provisions include:</p>
            <ol style="font-size: 20px;">
                <li><h4>Information Technology (IT) Act, 2000</h4></li>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Section 66E: </b>Covers the violation of privacy, including capturing, publishing, or transmitting private images of others without consent, with penalties of imprisonment up to 3 years and/or a fine.</li>
                    <li><b>Section 67: </b>Addresses publishing or transmitting obscene material in electronic form. Violations can result in imprisonment for up to 3 years and a fine for the first conviction, with harsher penalties for subsequent offenses.</li>
                    <li><b>Section 67A: </b>Deals with publishing or transmitting sexually explicit material in electronic form, with penalties including imprisonment for up to 5 years and a fine for the first conviction.</li>
                    <li><b>Section 67B: </b>Prohibits publishing or transmitting child pornographic material, imposing strict penalties, including imprisonment and fines.</li>
                    <li><b>Section 66C: </b>Addresses identity theft, including the fraudulent use of someone else's electronic signature, password, or unique identification features.</li>
                    <li><b>Section 66D: </b>Penalizes cheating by personation using computer resources, including impersonating others to deceive or defraud electronically.</li>
                </ul>
                <br>
                <li><h4>Indian Penal Code (IPC)</h4></li>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Section 354A: </b>Defines sexual harassment, including making sexually colored remarks or showing pornography against a woman's will, with penalties of up to 3 years imprisonment and fines.</li>
                    <li><b>Section 354D: </b>Addresses stalking, including monitoring a woman's internet or electronic communication, with penalties of up to 3 years for the first conviction.</li>
                    <li><b>Section 509: </b>Deals with words, gestures, or acts intended to insult the modesty of a woman, including online harassment, carrying penalties of up to 1 year imprisonment or fines.</li>
                </ul>
                <br>
                <li><h4>Criminal Law (Amendment) Act, 2013</h4></li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Introduced more stringent laws against stalking, voyeurism, and other forms of cyber harassment to address digital abuse and exploitation.</li>
                </ul>
            </ol>
